    <h1>Table</h1>
    <p class="text-l color-neutral-600">Data tables with token-controlled striping, borders, and a sticky-header option — wrap in <code>.table-wrapper</code> to handle horizontal overflow on narrow viewports.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2 class="heading-l">Basic table</h2>
    <p>Use <code>scope="col"</code> on header cells for proper screen reader semantics. A <code>&lt;caption&gt;</code> is rendered below the table and provides an accessible title.</p>
    
    <div class="padding-m margin-y-m background-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200">
